  "description": "Homeostasis is the maintenance of relatively stable internal conditions in a living system despite changes in the external environment. The term was coined by Walter Cannon in 1926, drawing on Claude Bernard's earlier concept of the *milieu intérieur* — the idea that the internal environment of an organism must remain constant for life to continue.",
